TERM_USAGE_DEFINITION_BASE.BASIC_TEXT:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252{\fonttbl{\f0}}\fs20\pard The number is automatically assigned to identify a specific base part configuration specification. A configuration specification is a unique combination of characteristics and options that is used in conjunction with a base part. The configuration of a base part can be initiated in IFS/Customer Orders, IFS/Shop Order and IFS/Dynamic Order Processing, as well as tested IFS/Manufacturing Standards using an Interim Order. If an asterisk (*) is displayed in this field, the part you are viewing does not have a configuration specification. This is either because it is not configurable or that it is configurable but that the configuration has not yet been defined.\par
\par
}

{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil ;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1033\f0\fs20 This is the short code for the site used for the order, requisition, agreement, part, or the like. A site is normally referred to as a geographic site, where, for instance, one company can have several sites; each one with a separate address. Sites are defined in the IFS/General Data for Inventory and Distribution component.\par
}

